An apostle at Enlightened Christian Gathering (ECG) church was shot dead while praying at a prayer mountain in South Africa.  The late Pastor of the church owned by controversial Malawian preacher Shepherd Bushiri, has been identified as Eric Bhuka. Bushiri who confirmed the shooting, wrote; “I am greatly pained and grieved to learn of the tragic shooting to death of Apostle Eric Bhuka, one of our ECG Pastors in South Africa. What’s even troubling is that our Apostle was shot at the prayer mountains, where he went to pray, preparing for the Great Entrance this Sunday. I celebrate you, Apostle Eric. You came, you preached, you won souls and, at your journey’s end, you have gone back to where we will all return after finishing the mission of preaching Jesus Christ.”  Source •Akinadewo (left) receiving the certificate from Oshodi Nigerians have been advised to imbibe the 'fruits of the Spirit' and fear God as laid down by Jesus Christ “so that insecurity, joblessness, economic crisis, political and social upheaval can become a thing of the past in the country”. Giving the admonition… In "Metro" Nobody is above scandals, not even tongue speaking, fiery pastors. Many Nigerian pastors have been involved in one scandal or the other. The most rampant is s*x scandals. One has to be careful when jumping from church seeking counsel because of those addressed as men of God are wolves in… In "Entertainment" ABUJA, (Sundiata Post) – Apostle Obii Pax-Harry has been conferred with the distinguished Daughter Award by the Women Christian Association of the Cathedral Church of All Saints, Egbu at their annual Women Christian Association conference in recognition of her selfless services, exemplary life and contribution to the church and humanity… In "News"